column5: Krates Marine receivership.  There will be an auction on boats there.  http://www.680news.com/2015/06/17/boats-on-sale-for-bargain-basement-prices-after-krates-marina-receivership/

Holy Good God!  From watching that video, a lot of people are going to lose their boats because they haven't picked them up.    How do you not take action right away.  Some of those boats look like they're pretty valuable.
That's crazy, can't seem to find the link they talked about in the video though...
My take on it is if the people can't afford or want to pay their repair and storage bill, to get their boats out of hock, then the boat isn't worth the cost of their repairs. Buyer beware!
I can't, for the life of me, find the link to the actual list of boats. Is it just me?
